2020-03-12
----------
    ROS Tutorials
    -------------
        http://wiki.ros.org/ROS/Tutorials
    How to add ros serial lib
    ------------------
        First add serial roslib to arduino environment
            http://wiki.ros.org/rosserial_arduino/Tutorials/Arduino%20IDE%20Setup

    How to work with command line arduino-cli
    -----------------------------------------
        1. Install arduino-cli 
            https://itp.nyu.edu/physcomp/resources/using-the-arduino-command-line-interface/
        2. $ arduino-cli core install arduino:avr 
        3. Compile
            https://arduino.github.io/arduino-cli/commands/arduino-cli_compile/

            $ arduino-cli compile -b arduino:avr:mega ../air_pump
        4. Upload
            $ arduino-cli upload -b arduino:avr:mega ../air_pump -p /dev/ttyUSB0
        5. Compile and Upload
            $ arduino-cli compile -b arduino:avr:mega -u -p /dev/ttyUSB0 ../air_pump -v
    How to work with rosserial_arduino
    -----------------------------------
        1. baudrate in python client 
            https://answers.ros.org/question/206972/baud-rate-parameter-in-rosserial_python-arduino/

        2. Terminal 1:
            $ roscore 
        3. Terminal 2:
            $ rosrun rosserial_python serial_node.py /dev/ttyUSB0 
            [INFO] [1584019417.780561]: ROS Serial Python Node
            [INFO] [1584019417.788995]: Connecting to /dev/ttyUSB0 at 57600 baud
            [INFO] [1584019420.025811]: Requesting topics...
            [INFO] [1584019420.058695]: Note: publish buffer size is 512 bytes
            [INFO] [1584019420.060620]: Setup publisher on chatter [std_msgs/String]
        3. Terminal 3:
            1. To echo the data to terminal:
                $ rostopic echo chatter
            2. To plot the data:
                $ rqt_plot
